ents.\\n\\n**1. Interface Determination:** The interface was derived directly from the golden testbench instantiation (`TopModule top_module1 (...)`) to ensure exact compatibility, resulting in ports `a, b, c, d` (inputs) and `out_sop, out_pos` (outputs).\\n\\n**2. DUT Logic:** The logic derived from the specification (which was already implemented in `previous_code`) was used for `TopModule`. A minor correction was made to align the input concatenation (`{d, c, b, a}`) with the interpretation of the input values (0 to 15) used in the reference module, where $V = d \\times 8 + c \\times 4 + b \\times 2 + a \\times 1$.\\n\\n**3. Testbench Improvement:**\\n    *   **Structure Maintenance:** All modules (`stimulus_gen`, `RefModule`, `TopModule`) and instantiations were maintained exactly as in the previous testbench.\\n    *   **Error Tracking & Display:** The error counting logic from the golden testbench was retained and corrected for syntax errors (e.g., fixing `sstats1` to `stats1`).\\n    *   **New Display Requirements:** A dedicated state capture block (`always @(posedge clk, negedge clk) if (!tb_match && stats1.errors == 1)`) was added to store the input/output values at the *first* mismatch time.\\n    *   **Reporting:** The final reporting block was completely rewritten to strictly adhere to the required output format:\\n        *   If errors exist, it displays: `SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y`, followed by detailed state dumps (inputs, ref outputs, DUT outputs) for SOP and POS separately, and finally a summary of the first overall mismatch.\\n        *   If no errors exist, it displays exactly: `SIMULATION PASSED`.\\n    *   **Signal Display:** Helper tasks (`display_signal`, `display_multi_signal`) were implemented to correctly show signals in both HEX and BINARY format, as required, for both 1-bit and 4-bit signals.\\n\\n**Advice to Avoid Syntax Errors:**\\n*   Ensure all module definitions are properly terminated with `endmodule`.\\n*   Use `logic` data types consistently for signals throughout the testbench.\\n*   Carefully check variable names across the entire testbench (e.g., ensure `stats1` is used everywhere instead of accidental typos like `sstats1`).\\n*   When dealing with complex final reporting logic, structure the checks (`if/else if`) sequentially to guarantee that only one final conclusion (PASSED or FAILED) is printed, and that the detailed failure report matches the specified format exactly.",\n    "interface": "module TopModule (\\n    input  logic a,\\n    input  logic b,\\n    input  logic c,\\n    input  logic d,\\n    output logic out_sop,\\n    output logic out_pos\\n);\\n",\n    "testbench": "`timescale 1 ps/1 ps\\n`define OK 12\\n`define INCORRECT 13\\n\\n// --- Stimulus Generator Module (Copied for completeness) ---\\nmodule stimulus_gen (\\n\\tinput clk,\\n\\toutput logic a, b, c, d,\\n\\toutput reg[511:0] wavedrom_title,\\n\\toutput reg wavedrom_enable,\\n\\tinput tb_match\\n);\\n\\t// Add two ports to module stimulus_gen:\\n\\t//    output [511:0] wavedrom_title\\n\\t//    output reg wavedrom_enable\\n\\ttask wavedrom_start(input[511:0] title = \\"\\");\\n\\tendtask\\t\\n\\ttask wavedrom_stop;\\n\\t\\t#1;\\n\\tendtask\\t\\n\\tbit fail = 0;\\n\\tbit fail1 = 0;\\n\\talways @(posedge clk, negedge clk)\\n\\t\\tif (!tb_match)\\n\\t\\t\\tfail = 1;\\n\\n\\tinitial begin\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 0;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 1;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 2;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 4;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 5;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 6;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 7;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 9;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 10;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 13;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 14;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) {a,b,c,d} <= 15;\\n\\t\\t@(posedge clk) fail1 = fail;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\t//@(negedge clk) wavedrom_start();\\n\\t\\tfor (int i=0;i<16;i++)\\n\\t\\t\\t@(posedge clk)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t{a,b,c,d} <= i;\\n\\t\\t//@(negedge clk) wavedrom_stop();\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\trepeat(50) @(posedge clk, negedge clk)\\n\\t\\t\\t{a,b,c,d} <= $random;\\n\\t\\t\\n\\t\\tif (fail && ~fail1)\\n\\t\\t\\t$display(\\"Hint: Your circuit passes on the 12 required input combinations, but doesn\'t match the don\'t-care cases. Are you using minimal SOP and POS?\\");\\n\\n\\t\\t$finish;\\n\\tend\\n\\tendmodule\\n\\n// --- Reference Module (Golden Reference Logic) ---\\nmodule RefModule (\\n    input  logic a,\\n    input  logic b,\\n    input  logic c,\\n    input  logic d,\\n    output logic out_sop,\\n    output logic out_pos\\n);\\n\\t// Inputs map to value V = d*8 + c*4 + b*2 + a*1\\n\\tlogic [3:0] V;\\n\\tassign V = {d, c, b, a};\\n\\n\\t// out_sop (True when V is 2, 7, or 15)\\n\\tout_sop = (V == 4\'b0010) || (V == 4\'b0111) || (V == 4\'b1111);\\n\\n\\t// out_pos (True when V is 2, 7, or 15, since this is the complement of the 0-set)\\n\\tout_pos = (V == 4\'b0010) || (V == 4\'b0111) || (V == 4\'b1111);\\n\\nendmodule\\n\\n// --- DUT Module (TopModule) ---\\nmodule TopModule (\\n    input  logic a,\\n    input  logic b,\\n    input  logic c,\\n    input  logic d,\\n    output logic out_sop,\\n    output logic out_pos\\n);\\n\\t// Concatenate inputs to form a 4-bit vector where \'a\' is LSB, \'d\' is MSB (matching V = d*8 + c*4 + b*2 + a*1)\\n\\tlogic [3:0] inputs = {d, c, b, a};\\n\\n\\t// Combinational logic implementation using case statement\\n\\talways @* begin\\n\\t\\t// Default assignments: Assume 0 for SOP and 1 for POS if not explicitly defined\\n\\t\\tout_sop = 1\'b0;\\n\\t\\tout_pos = 1\'b1;\\n\\n\\t\\tcase (inputs)\\n\\t\\t\\t// Required 1s for out_sop (Minterms: 2, 7, 15)\\n\\t\\t\\t4\'d2: begin\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tout_sop = 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t4\'d7: begin\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tout_sop = 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\t\\t\\t4\'d15: begin\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tout_sop = 1\'b1;\\n\\t\\t\\tend\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t// Required 0s for out_pos (Maxterms: 0, 1, 4, 5, 6